						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the same shrine.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-pāṇḍyadēva: Year 7 = 1272 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is very much damaged and is incomplete. It appears to record a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">kuḍinīṅgā-dēvadāna</hi> and a gift of paddy to provide for food offerings and to do some services probably to the deity Avināśiyāḷuḍaiya-nāyanār. Mention is made of the premises of the temple of this deity and of a street called <hi rend="italic">Vikkiramachōḻan-tiruvīdi.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
